translated: Österdahl, Georg, captain, director, Gothenburg, b. 1/9/90 in Örebro to organ builder A.O. and Augusta Pettersson. — Graduated from high school in Stockholm in 1909, HHS 1913-1914. Employed at Clarholm & Bergman in Gothenburg in 1920, became a partner in 1925 and managing director after the company's decision to become a limited company in 1930. Also served as managing director in Biläg. Verkst. A-B since 1922, Iwar Janson Kolonialvaru A-B since 1932, Benlock A-B since 1934 and Nya Hand. A-B Carl Arfvidson in Vara since 1942. Chairman of the board for A-B Kemiifa, A-B Folkbilar, Swedish Wholesalers Association, Grand Duchy Imports Council and Investigation Institute from 1941-1945. Chairman of Swedish Wholesale Grocery Association, Gothenburg Wholesalers Association, board member of Gothenburg Frihamn A-B, Gothenburg Merchants Association, Gothenburg Flour Association, Western Sweden Sugar Wholesale Association, Swedish Colonial Grocery Association, A-B Swedish ColonialgTOss., A-B Godsemottagning, International Trade Chamber, president of the International Colonialengineers Association. Member of the board for S:t Jörgen Hospital, chairman of the board for Gothenburg City Theatre. Recipient of Royal Order of the North Star, Royal Order of Vasa.

awards: Royal Order of the North Star
